reviews.title: Outlaw practices and a wheel clamp
reviews.text:
If you ever want to experience what it's like to end up in a bad western movie, Ribhouse Texas in Epe is the perfect location. With the whole team spending hundreds of euros on food and drinks (the ribs weren’t even that impressive, to be honest), neatly arranged for one colleague to stay sober so everyone could get home safely. 1 Car left standing.

And what do you get? No thank you, no “nice that you are responsible with alcohol”...! But no... outside the sheriff of Ribhouse Texas was already ready with his wheel clamp. It was like we got into a bad cowboy movie. No understanding, no conversation, just: paying a ransom to get your own car back in an almost empty parking lot , because apparently more visitors already know that it is better to park your car outside the site...

And apparently they're not only good at smoking spare ribs but also at extortion practices. Even after explanation: zero understanding, just dock.
So yes, Texas it certainly was: saloon prices inside, outlaw practices outside.

We never come back here and wonder whether the one-time ransom was worth the experience shared with it.

Service also always good, good Service and generally good staff.

The theme evenings/weeks are really great.

reviews.title: Not gluten free as claimed
reviews.text: Food wasx delicious, but, as promised what was possible: not gluten-free.  Been sick for a week.  Responsibility was placed on me, I would have eaten of the bread on the table.  This has been a while.  I hope the host has better customer service now than back then.

reviews.title: Operation
reviews.text:
We have been with two families very cozy but the service was very poor.
Standing at the table with the wrong food which is not for us.
No tray for the spare ribs bones and no wipes for your hands. 
We eat here several times a year but we keep asking about it.

reviews.title: Delicious food in a special ambience
reviews.text: We've been coming here for years. The food is good and the restaurant itself is an experience. I have a milk allergy. That has been seriously considered. As a result, the food was not only delicious (ribs and ladysteak), but also “safe”. The only downside: when it is full, it is very loud.

It's and remain kids hey, have all been young. I think/thought it was a pity how that dear gentleman addressed us and especially she whole tone did not please me with them hat on.

reviews.title: Fun with the family
reviews.text: Great food with the family. Something for everyone. Very friendly staff and nice decoration. Portions are ample and desserts were delicious

reviews.title: The food is good, if you want to wait forever and then be chased away...
reviews.text:
The food was delicious, but that was also allowed. We really had to wait forever for every course. 
Waiting an hour for the main course for 5 people is really unacceptable, especially at these prices!

The side dishes were brought a lot later and did not correspond at all to what was ordered. A correction / addition of the side dishes, which was strongly requested, was never brought at all...

After looking at the dessert menu, we were told that we could get desserts and coffee, as long as we would go to another table, otherwise we had to get out because the table was needed for new guests. Unheard of this!
You are terribly slow and because of that we are taken away from our table when ‘it is money made’. While several other tables were available. 

And for that pleasure we pay almost € 300! I really don't have words for this...

reviews.title: never again...
reviews.text: It was a very hot day today. That's why I called in advance how it was. Porch would be without sails, so nice with wind and without sun. Turns out more than half the sails were closed. According to supervisor (with a fairly aggressive approach), this was a lot of work. After insisting he opened a sail anyway (90 seconds work) Meat was very moderate. Waited over an hour and a half for main course. We never eat here but never again

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: Your family-friendly guide to fall fun in Michigan

seoInfo.metaDescription: Grab your crew and cozy sweaters—harvest season is in full swing

I’ve always loved train travel. There’s something special about settling into a window seat and watching the landscape drift past. And as a wheelchair user, that joy only grows when the journey feels easy: level boarding, space to move, and the kind of accessibility that lets you fully relax. For me, the best train rides—like weaving through the Tuscan countryside on Trenitalia—are never just a way to get from A to B; they're part of the adventure.

randomContentList.sponsorDisplayName: the More to Jamaica Community-Based Tourism Project

seoInfo.metaDescription: Experience Jamaica through local eyes. From Maroon traditions and family-run farms to artisan workshops and river tubing adventures, these are the moments that bring the island’s soul to life. Across the island, communities are opening their doors and inviting you in. Travel deeper with locally-led experiences and see a side of Jamaica some visitors miss: authentic, unforgettable, and full of heart.

articleContent.title: 10 unique experiences you can only have in Reykjavik

seoInfo.metaDescription: I’ll start by saying I’m not usually a group tour kind of traveler. I prefer wandering off on my own, stumbling into cafés, taking on hikes, and meeting plenty of locals along the way. But the one place I lift this preference is Iceland, specifically Reykjavik. After more than a dozen visits, I’ve learned that the best way to see some of this country’s incredible natural landscapes is under the direction of a professional. Iceland’s beauty is a thick layer above the very real danger that comes with existing on a volcanic piece of land in the middle of the ocean.
These picks have major atmosphere for solo travelers—and great food, of course.

articleContent.title: 8 collapsible water bottles to help you pack light

seoInfo.metaDescription: Stay hydrated with these collapsible water bottles that won't take up precious packing space

articleContent.title: 5 perfect days in New York City

seoInfo.metaDescription: More than 60 million people visit New York City every year, and a huge percentage of them only hit the big sites—Times Square, the Empire State Building, etc. I get it: They’re iconic. But as someone who has lived in this city for more than 30 years, I’m here to tell you that you’re missing out if you don’t mix in some off-the-beaten path locations. Luckily, five days gives you plenty of time to do just that.

articleContent.title: Celebrate the best of Osaka’s food and nightlife with Suntory

seoInfo.metaDescription: If you’ve ever found yourself standing in line for hours at a famous ramen spot in Japan, you’d probably agree that food and drinks are a big part of why we travel. It’s one of the best ways to get a glimpse into a destination's culture, traditions, and history, whether it’s through its local dishes, ingredients, or culinary customs. But if you really want to embrace local culture, there’s no better way than over a glass. Share a drink with locals, friends, and fellow travelers, and experience the camaraderie, stories, and traditions that make up the heart of a destination, forging deeper connections along the way.

reviews.title: Fine but not special.
reviews.text: Delicious food. However, prices are rising explosively and at the same time portions are getting smaller. That ratio was better in the past.

reviews.title: Eating at Ribhouse Texas
reviews.text:
A cozy restaurant! Nicely decorated, everything in Texas style!
Peanut shells could be thrown on the floor, food tasted delicious, despite the crowds we didn't have to wait long (it's smart to book well in advance).

reviews.title: What a disappointment for such a nice themed restaurant! Over the top!
reviews.text:
It is of course quite an experience to eat at the Ribhouse Texas, but the quality of the food is poor compared to the price! The attention paid to the products could also be better!
The open wines are downright bad! The meat deserves more attention on the grill, this time with way too many spices that were burnt! The tuna beforehand was the bright spot of the evening!

reviews.title: not to be repeated
reviews.text: Mass is cash register. Mixed grill, the spareribs could not be removed from the bone and the steak was tough. This is indicated at the operator. I received the answer that I had not chosen the correct menu because the meat would be of lower quality. The restaurant has filled out a contact form on their website, but unfortunately no response.

reviews.title: cozy restaurant
reviews.text:
Very nicely decorated restaurant with friendly staff.
You don't have to wait long for food or drinks.

reviews.title: 1:30h Waiting and still no food.
reviews.text:
I‘ve come here for diner with my Wife and after 20 minutes waiting we decided to ask if we can order food. 
(We were the first customers there..) 
1:30h later we still had no food, just drinks. 

It was unbelievable.

reviews.title: Wonderful
reviews.text: We had a wonderful evening with very good food. The waitresses were very kindly en joyful. They take good care if us. While we were waiting there was a magician by our table whit some lovely trics  a wonderfull evening.

reviews.title: Great place
reviews.text:
Excellent restaurant, friendly service and great food! Thoroughly enjoyed our night. 

If you're close and enjoy good meat, go there!

reviews.title: If you like meat....
reviews.text: Always good if you like meat. Decent ribs, proper steaks and a cozy western athmosphere. And ofcourse the peanuts which shells you may throw on the floor.

reviews.title: Great Steaks - Great for families& fun
reviews.text:
Great Experience - Unusual  steak house with excellent food and quirky decor - Great for families , and fun.
Recommended

reviews.title: Great ribhouse with good food
reviews.text: We went here for a little celebration. The staff was very kind and polite. We started with the Buffalo Wings. Those where excellent. I've never had them better anywhere. The ribs we had where good. They mixed the plates, so I had my friends order and vice versa, but nothing we could fix by ourself. The Chocolate Cheesecake we had for desert wasn't that much of my taste, but the Icecream that comes with is was so good. The price is very good compared to the food. The decoration of the interior is very nice. You really feel yourself in a Western Saloon. The staff is dressed as cowboys, which gives it a nice touch.

reviews.title: Excellent steakhouse
reviews.text: Friends who lived locally took us here. Excellent range of steaks and other meats. Even has vegetarian but not sure this is the place for a vegetarian! We were sat not far from where they cook the steaks which was very interesting. Big place, very busy but well worth it. Excellent meal!

reviews.title: Good place and good meat
reviews.text: Funny place to go with the family. Good food and service. You feel like being in Texas! Ribbs are very good and all other meat.

reviews.title: You can throw peanuts on the floor!
reviews.text: Great restaurant to go to with family or friends. The kids love it (you can throw peanuts on the floor)

reviews.title: Good steak, but crowded and loud
reviews.text:
The restaurant (exteriour, interiour, staff clothing, etc.) is in "Western" style. Very well done, but a bit over the top for me. This is not a place for vegetarians or vegans, you go here for the meat, which is excellent.
We were with a group of 8 on a busy time. That combined with pretty loud music made a conversation almost impossible. Also, it took a while before our orders were taken and drinks and food were served. 
As said, the meat was excellent, worth a visit.

reviews.title: Humorous theming and good food
reviews.text:
Before going here, I'd only been to the original Ribhouse Texas in Voorst, and my friends and I really liked that one. For both places, I'm not a huge fan of their ribs (I'm also not a fan of ribs in general in most cases), but their tomato cream soup is good, but the jacket potato - especially with their creamy garlic sauce - is fantastic. The sixteen of us got free bread upon sitting down, though it wasn't refilled. :p

It was only EUR 6.25 to have the soup (4 EUR) and the jacket potato (2.25 EUR), so if you're a small eater, you can enjoy this place too. I also liked the decor of this Ribhouse Texas better than the one in Voorst, as here both the inside and the outside looked nice. :)

reviews.title: Cool !!
reviews.text:
Cool place for a family dinner. The concept is very nice and as someone who have been in the U.S. many times, I have to say they are doing a really good job. Expect to eat an "hard core" steaks. Pure meet. Not for vegetarians...
The atmosphere is very loose and happy. 
We loved it.

reviews.title: "Extra" hot and spicy ribs
reviews.text: If you like "extra" hot and spicy spare ribs, you need to tell staffs. Otherwise you will get their normal hot and spicy which for us is way too plain. Starter is good. Dessert is awesome. Restaurant atmosphere is really nice, both indoor and outdoor.

reviews.title: Proper meat place!
reviews.text: If your like me and you love big juicy steaks then you'll love it here. The resturant has a great astmophere, the staff are dressed as cowboys and cowgirls and service was surprisingly quick, it was packed when we went so I recommend reserving a table. We turned up as a couple and had to wait until a table came free. Like all these places it's not cheap but also not extortion. Would come back!

reviews.title: Nice place, decent food
reviews.text: If you feel like having a proper stake in a western setting than this is a nice plave to go to. Expect the place to be busy, the price is fair and the food is decent and the place lends itself for things like birhtday parties as well. It is also a big place so if your looking for an intimate quit dinner you need to skip this place.

reviews.title: Amazing, a must visit.
reviews.text:
Went to visit some family, we wanted a nice night out with a good meal. The staff were fantastic, considering most our party only spoke English they were very patient and helpful. 
The steaks are cooked over coals, and tasted great, 
Entertainment was perfect, not too loud so you could have a conversation but loud enough to enjoy if you so wished.

reviews.title: Ok food for a mid-range prize
reviews.text: During one of my birthdays I went there and the ambience is really good but the quality of the food is ok. It is good enough but not amazing.

reviews.title: Great steak in Texas atmosphere
reviews.text: We ended up in this restaurant for a late anniversary celebration. It is situated outside Epe with a large parking lot which was packed (always a good sign). The restaurant is cabin style with various Texas style signs. We were received by a cowboy and escorted to our table by a cowgirl, not bad. The menu is typical Texas (or US) al kind off big steaks, the biggest is  1 kg T-bone. Maybe because the place was packed but it took a long time to get our steaks on the table. The quality was good as where the typical side dices. It was a cool experience, will go back.

reviews.title: burning meat
reviews.text:
amazing that this restaurant is still that much visited .
it might be a good eatery for families with small children but that is all.

reviews.title: Great fun and food for the whole family
reviews.text: This is a very nice family US country style restaurant in the area. Nice steaks and also good hamburgers and hotdogs for the kids. All waiters are dressed up. You really get a show if you order the largest T-bone steak or a birthday cake/ice cream.

reviews.title: Steakhouse style family restaurant
reviews.text:
If you like to eat out in a "Real cowboy style \ all american steakhouse", go to one out of 7 Ribhouse Texas restaurants in the east of the Netherlands.

Be very sure you book a table in advande during weekends, in spite of the fact Ribhouses, run 3 dinner cycles\ moments as from 5 PM, it seems to be Always booked.

The locations are "all american style comboy restaurants". While waiting on your food music and the interior make you feel "at home in this yankee doodle restaunrant". 

Do walk with your kids to the "open grill'\ firy kitchen", where chefs are making the steaks for you.

Food quality is great, the rib's are delicious. Multimple choice in menu;s , both suitable for kids and adults, will make the visit fior familiies an event.

Staff is well trained, from time to time they really complete the experience , when special dishes or moments needs some celebration.

reviews.title: Wild west
reviews.text: A part of the wild west seems to have been transplanted to the Netherlands. The atmosphere is amazing. You really feel like you've been transplanted to the desert. The food is good, grilled, lovely.

reviews.title: Great ribs!
reviews.text: Just been on my second visit and I love this place! Wonderful spicy ribs, attentive staff and a fun atmosphere! Prices are reasonable and you get a doggy bag home if you cannot manage to finish your meal, which is almost unheard of in the Netherlands!

reviews.title: Texas in Epe?
reviews.text: A fun restaurant for young and old. For non-vegetarians carnovorians this place is local must. Excellent meat quality in ambiance of fake "Western style". Personnel are highly efficient and friendly, definitely contributing to the relaxing atmospere.

reviews.title: good food for not to much money
reviews.text:
Ok, it's not the best steakhouse in the world, but it's quite good for the price you pay!
The atmosphere is a bit 'Western' and the service is ok.
If you just want to hang out with friends and have a piece of steak this is a quite accaptable place to go!

reviews.title: Nice atmosphere - different in the positive way!
reviews.text: If you like something different but do not want to give in on quality for a reasonable price... This could be your choice!
